TITLE: Installing Symfony HttpKernel via Composer - Terminal
DESCRIPTION: Installs the symfony/http-kernel package using Composer, which is the recommended PHP dependency manager for Symfony. This is the prerequisite for working with HttpKernel, ensuring all required PHP dependencies are fetched automatically. The command should be executed in the root directory of your PHP project and requires Composer to be installed globally.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/http_kernel.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terminal
CODE:
```
$ composer require symfony/http-kernel
```

