TITLE: Creating a Form Type Class in Symfony
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a basic form type class in Symfony. It shows the structure of a form builder method, including adding form fields with different options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/forms.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Symfony\Component\Form\FormBuilderInterface;

class TaskType extends AbstractType
{
    public function buildForm(FormBuilderInterface $builder, array $options): void
    {
        $builder
            // if you don't define field options, you can omit the second argument
            ->add('task')
            // if you define field options, pass NULL as second argument
            ->add('dueDate', null, ['required' => false])
            ->add('save', SubmitType::class)
        ;
    }
}
```

