TITLE: Creating JSON Response in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows two ways to create a JSON response in Symfony: using the Response class and using the JsonResponse class.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/http_foundation.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_33

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
use Symfony\Component\HttpFoundation\Response;

$response = new Response();
$response->setContent(json_encode([
    'data' => 123,
]));
$response->headers->set('Content-Type', 'application/json');
```

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
use Symfony\Component\HttpFoundation\JsonResponse;

// if you know the data to send when creating the response
$response = new JsonResponse(['data' => 123]);

// if you don't know the data to send or if you want to customize the encoding options
