TITLE: Implementing Custom Constraint Validator in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to create a custom constraint validator class that extends ConstraintValidator. It includes error handling and the actual validation logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/validation/custom_constraint.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
// src/Validator/ContainsAlphanumericValidator.php
namespace App\Validator;

use Symfony\Component\Validator\Constraint;
use Symfony\Component\Validator\ConstraintValidator;
use Symfony\Component\Validator\Exception\UnexpectedTypeException;
use Symfony\Component\Validator\Exception\UnexpectedValueException;

class ContainsAlphanumericValidator extends ConstraintValidator
{
    public function validate(mixed $value, Constraint $constraint): void
    {
        if (!$constraint instanceof ContainsAlphanumeric) {
            throw new UnexpectedTypeException($constraint, ContainsAlphanumeric::class);
        }

        if (null === $value || '' === $value) {
            return;
        }

        if (!is_string($value)) {
            throw new UnexpectedValueException($value, 'string');
        }

        if ('strict' === $constraint->mode) {
            // ...
        }

        if (preg_match('/^[a-zA-Z0-9]+$/', $value, $matches)) {
            return;
        }

        $this->context->buildViolation($constraint->message)
            ->setParameter('{{ string }}', $value)
            ->addViolation();
    }
}
```

