TITLE: Evaluating XPath Expressions with Symfony DomCrawler in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the Crawler's evaluate and filterXPath features to run XPath expressions and compute results like attribute substrings or counts. Examples include extracting IDs, counting elements, and returning new Crawler instances based on XPath queries. The behavior varies depending on the XPath return type.
