TITLE: Configuring Remember Me with Symfony Security (PHP Configurator)
DESCRIPTION: This PHP snippet uses the Symfony PHP config closure pattern to define 'rememberMe' settings for the main firewall. It specifies the secret, cookie lifetime, and the optional 'alwaysRememberMe' flag. Place in config/packages/security.php, ensuring proper use of the Symfony\Config\SecurityConfig namespace. Dependencies include Symfony's PHP-based configuration, ensuring symbolic parameter values (like '%kernel.secret%') resolve accurately. Key parameters control whether all users get persistent login cookies or only on opt-in.
