TITLE: Passing Variables to Expressions in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to pass external data, including objects, into an expression during evaluation. The second argument to `evaluate()` is an associative array where keys are variable names used in the expression (e.g., 'fruit') and values are their corresponding PHP values (e.g., the `$apple` object). The expression can then access properties and methods of these passed variables.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/expression_language.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_5

