TITLE: Handling Long Processes with Lock Verification in Symfony
DESCRIPTION: Example showing a transaction pattern with lock verification. It demonstrates acquiring a lock, starting a transaction, performing a long operation, and then verifying the lock is still held before committing, with rollback handling if the lock was lost.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/lock.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// If we cannot acquire ourselves, it means some other process is already working on it
if (!$lock->acquire()) {
    return;
}

$this->beginTransaction();

// Perform a very long process that might exceed TTL of the lock

if ($lock->isAcquired()) {
    // Still all good, no other instance has acquired the lock in the meantime, we're safe
    $this->commit();
} else {
    // Bummer! Our lock has apparently exceeded TTL and another process has started in
    // the meantime so it's not safe for us to commit.
    $this->rollback();
    throw new \Exception('Process failed');
}
```

