TITLE: Registering Service Using Non-Static Factory - PHP Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Uses PHP configuration to register a NewsletterManagerFactory as a service and then create the NewsletterManager by referencing a method of that factory service. This leverages the 'factory' method to inject an instance created by another service, rather than using a static method. Intended for advanced PHP service configuration in 'config/services.php'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/service_container/factories.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_14

