TITLE: Creating a Symfony Form with Default Values in a Controller (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to set default values for form fields when creating a form within a Symfony controller. An array containing default data (`$defaults`) is passed as the first argument to the `createFormBuilder` shortcut method. This pre-populates the form fields when rendered. Requires the Symfony FrameworkBundle.
