TITLE: Using Expressions in Service Factory Definitions - Symfony YAML - yaml
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates defining factories using expression language in Symfony YAML configuration, allowing conditional logic or argument retrieval for service instantiation. Requires Symfony's expression language support and proper parameter/service definitions. Demonstrates conditional selection of tracer or default newsletter service and use of the arg() function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/service_container/factories.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
# config/services.yaml
services:
    App\Email\NewsletterManagerInterface:
        # use the "tracable_newsletter" service when debug is enabled, "newsletter" otherwise.
        # "@=" indicates that this is an expression
        factory: '@=parameter("kernel.debug") ? service("tracable_newsletter") : service("newsletter")'

    # you can use the arg() function to retrieve an argument from the definition
    App\Email\NewsletterManagerInterface:
        factory: "@=arg(0).createNewsletterManager() ?: service(\"default_newsletter_manager\")"
        arguments:
            - '@App\Email\NewsletterManagerFactory'

```

