TITLE: Implementing LeapYear Model in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Model class containing business logic for determining if a given year is a leap year, demonstrating separation of business logic from controllers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/create_framework/separation_of_concerns.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
namespace Calendar\Model;

class LeapYear
{
    public function isLeapYear(?int $year = null): bool
    {
        if (null === $year) {
            $year = date('Y');
        }

        return 0 == $year % 400 || (0 == $year % 4 && 0 != $year % 100);
    }
}
```

