TITLE: Generating a Version 3 Name-Based UUID (MD5) in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to generate a deterministic UUIDv3 using a namespace (predefined like `Uuid::NAMESPACE_OID` or a custom one) and an arbitrary name string. The `Uuid::v3()` method hashes the concatenation of the namespace and name using MD5. The result is an instance of `Symfony\Component\Uid\UuidV3`.
