TITLE: Configuring Pseudo-localization in Symfony with PHP
DESCRIPTION: This PHP configuration sets up the pseudo-localization feature in Symfony's Translation component. It enables character accents, brackets wrapping, text expansion, HTML tag preservation, and specifies which HTML attributes should be localized.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/translation.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_59

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// config/packages/translation.php
use Symfony\Config\FrameworkConfig;

return static function (FrameworkConfig $framework) {
    // ...
    $framework
        ->translator()
            ->pseudoLocalization()
                // replace characters by their accented version
                ->accents(true)
                // wrap strings with brackets
                ->brackets(true)
                // controls how many extra characters are added to make text longer
                ->expansionFactor(1.4)
                // maintain the original HTML tags of the translated contents
                ->parseHtml(true)
                // also translate the contents of these HTML attributes
                ->localizableHtmlAttributes(['title'])
    ;
};
```

