TITLE: Customizing CSRF Protection Options within a Symfony Form Type
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to configure CSRF protection settings specifically for an individual form within its Form Type class (`TaskType`). The `configureOptions` method allows overriding global defaults by setting options like `csrf_protection` (to enable/disable), `csrf_field_name` (the hidden field's name, defaults to `_token`), and `csrf_token_id` (a unique string used to generate the token, enhancing security per form).
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/security/csrf.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// src/Form/TaskType.php
namespace App\Form;

// ...
use App\Entity\Task;
use Symfony\Component\OptionsResolver\OptionsResolver;

class TaskType extends AbstractType
{
    // ...

    public function configureOptions(OptionsResolver $resolver): void
    {
        $resolver->setDefaults([
            'data_class'      => Task::class,
            // enable/disable CSRF protection for this form
            'csrf_protection' => true,
            // the name of the hidden HTML field that stores the token
            'csrf_field_name' => '_token',
            // an arbitrary string used to generate the value of the token
            // using a different string for each form improves its security
            'csrf_token_id'   => 'task_item',
        ]);
    }

    // ...
}
```

