TITLE: Checking Value Acceptance with accepts()
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates using the `accepts()` method on a `Type` object to determine if a given value conforms to the defined type. This method provides a way to validate values against a type definition. Examples show checking simple integer types and union types (int|string). This method was introduced in Symfony 7.3.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/type_info.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$type = Type::int();
// check if the type accepts a given value
$type->accepts(123); // true
$type->accepts('z'); // false

$type = Type::union(Type::string(), Type::int());
// now the second check is true because the union type accepts either an int or a string value
$type->accepts(123); // true
$type->accepts('z'); // true
```

