TITLE: Using Service Aliases for Autowiring (YAML, XML, PHP)
DESCRIPTION: These configuration examples demonstrate how to use service aliases to facilitate autowiring when a service's ID does not match its class name. An alias is created with the ID matching the class name (`App\Util\Rot13Transformer`) and points to the actual service ID (`app.rot13.transformer`). This allows autowiring based on the class type-hint to resolve correctly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/service_container/autowiring.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
# config/services.yaml
services:
    # ...

    # the id is not a class, so it won't be used for autowiring
    app.rot13.transformer:
        class: App\Util\Rot13Transformer
        # ...

    # but this fixes it!
    # the "app.rot13.transformer" service will be injected when
    # an App\Util\Rot13Transformer type-hint is detected
    App\Util\Rot13Transformer: '@app.rot13.transformer'
```

LANGUAGE: xml
CODE:
```
<!-- config/services.xml -->
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<container xmlns="http://symfony.com/schema/dic/services"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://symfony.com/schema/dic/services https://symfony.com/schema/dic/services/services-1.0.xsd">

    <services>
        <!-- ... -->

        <service id="app.rot13.transformer" class="App\Util\Rot13Transformer" autowire="true"/>
        <service id="App\Util\Rot13Transformer" alias="app.rot13.transformer"/>
    </services>
</container>
```

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// config/services.php
namespace Symfony\Component\DependencyInjection\Loader\Configurator;

use App\Util\Rot13Transformer;

return function(ContainerConfigurator $container): void {
    // ...

    // the id is not a class, so it won't be used for autowiring
    $services->set('app.rot13.transformer', Rot13Transformer::class)
        ->autowire();

    // but this fixes it!
    // the "app.rot13.transformer" service will be injected when
    // an App\Util\Rot13Transformer type-hint is detected
    $services->alias(Rot13Transformer::class, 'app.rot13.transformer');
};
```

