TITLE: Fetching Currency Rounding Increments using Symfony Intl in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates retrieving the standard rounding increment and the cash rounding increment for specific currencies (INR, CAD) using `Currencies::getRoundingIncrement()` and `Currencies::getCashRoundingIncrement()`. This highlights how cash transactions might require rounding to specific increments (like 5 cents for CAD) due to the elimination of smaller coin denominations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/intl.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// Indian rupee defines the same value for both
$roundingIncrement = Currencies::getRoundingIncrement('INR');         // returns: 0
$cashRoundingIncrement = Currencies::getCashRoundingIncrement('INR'); // returns: 0

// Canadian dollar defines different values because they have eliminated
// the smaller coins (1-cent and 2-cent) and prices in cash must be rounded to
// 5 cents (e.g. if price is 7.42 you pay 7.40; if price is 7.48 you pay 7.50)
$roundingIncrement = Currencies::getRoundingIncrement('CAD');         // returns: 0
