TITLE: Initializing ProxyAdapter with PSR-6 Cache Pool in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create and configure a ProxyAdapter instance that wraps a PSR-6 compliant cache pool. The adapter allows for optional namespace prefixing and default cache lifetime configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/cache/adapters/proxy_adapter.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Psr\Cache\CacheItemPoolInterface;
use Symfony\Component\Cache\Adapter\ProxyAdapter;

// create your own cache pool instance that implements
// the PSR-6 CacheItemPoolInterface
$psr6CachePool = ...

$cache = new ProxyAdapter(

    // a cache pool instance
    CacheItemPoolInterface $psr6CachePool,

    // a string prefixed to the keys of the items stored in this cache
    $namespace = '',

    // the default lifetime (in seconds) for cache items that do not define their
    // own lifetime, with a value 0 causing items to be stored indefinitely (i.e.
    // until the cache is cleared)
    $defaultLifetime = 0
);
```

