TITLE: Service Decoration in PHP Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Example of implementing the Decorator pattern in PHP configuration. The 'decorate()' method is used to override a service while keeping the original service available as '.inner'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/service_container/service_decoration.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// config/services.php
namespace Symfony\Component\DependencyInjection\Loader\Configurator;

use App\DecoratingMailer;
use App\Mailer;

return function(ContainerConfigurator $container): void {
    $services = $container->services();

    $services->set(Mailer::class);

    $services->set(DecoratingMailer::class)
        // overrides the App\Mailer service
        // but that service is still available as ".inner"
        ->decorate(Mailer::class);
};
```

