TITLE: Registering Static Factory Service - PHP Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to register the NewsletterManager service through code in 'config/services.php', using Symfony's ContainerConfigurator API. The 'factory' method sets the static factory class and method for service creation. Requires corresponding PHP classes to be present, and is suitable for advanced configuration scenarios.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/service_container/factories.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// config/services.php
namespace Symfony\Component\DependencyInjection\Loader\Configurator;

use App\Email\NewsletterManager;
use App\Email\NewsletterManagerStaticFactory;

return function(ContainerConfigurator $container): void {
    $services = $container->services();

    $services->set(NewsletterManager::class)
        // the first argument is the class and the second argument is the static method
        ->factory([NewsletterManagerStaticFactory::class, 'createNewsletterManager']);
};

```

