TITLE: Registering a Custom Translation Loader Service
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to register a custom translation loader service (`App\Translation\MyCustomLoader`) in Symfony using YAML, XML, and PHP configuration. The service must be tagged with `translation.loader` and requires an `alias` option, which defines the file suffix (e.g., 'bin') for translation files this loader handles.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/reference/dic_tags.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
.. code-block:: yaml

    services:
        App\Translation\MyCustomLoader:
            tags:
                - { name: translation.loader, alias: bin }
```

LANGUAGE: xml
CODE:
```
.. code-block:: xml

    <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
    <container xmlns="http://symfony.com/schema/dic/services"
        xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
        xsi:schemaLocation="http://symfony.com/schema/dic/services
            https://symfony.com/schema/dic/services/services-1.0.xsd">

        <services>
            <service id="App\Translation\MyCustomLoader">
                <tag name="translation.loader" alias="bin"/>
            </service>
        </services>
    </container>
```

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
.. code-block:: php

    use App\Translation\MyCustomLoader;

    $container
        ->register(MyCustomLoader::class)
        ->addTag('translation.loader', ['alias' => 'bin'])
    ;
```

