TITLE: Customizing Error Path with UniqueEntity Constraint using PHP API in Symfony
DESCRIPTION: Example of setting the errorPath option with the UniqueEntity constraint using PHP Validator API to control where validation error messages appear when validating uniqueness across multiple fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/reference/constraints/UniqueEntity.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// src/Entity/Service.php
namespace App\Entity;

use App\Entity\Host;
use Symfony\Bridge\Doctrine\Validator\Constraints\UniqueEntity;
use Symfony\Component\Validator\Mapping\ClassMetadata;

class Service
{
    public Host $host;
    public int $port;

    public static function loadValidatorMetadata(ClassMetadata $metadata): void
    {
        $metadata->addConstraint(new UniqueEntity([
            'fields' => ['host', 'port'],
            'message' => 'This port is already in use on that host.',
            'errorPath' => 'port',
        ]));
    }
}
```

