TITLE: Accepting Multiline Answers in Symfony Console - PHP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to allow multiline answers in a Symfony Console question by enabling the setMultiline(true) option on the Question object. It depends on symfony/console and typical Symfony command execution context. The answer variable will contain the full multiline input, ending on Ctrl-D (Unix) or Ctrl-Z (Windows); input stops only when end-of-transmission is received.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/console/helpers/questionhelper.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Symfony\Component\Console\Question\Question;

// ...
public function execute(InputInterface $input, OutputInterface $output): int
{
    // ...
    $helper = $this->getHelper('question');

    $question = new Question('How do you solve world peace?');
    $question->setMultiline(true);

    $answer = $helper->ask($input, $output, $question);

    // ... do something with the answer

    return Command::SUCCESS;
}

```

