TITLE: Utilizing Isser/Hasser Methods with PropertyAccessor (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Explains that if a getter isn't found, `PropertyAccessor::getValue()` looks for isser (e.g., `isAuthor()`) or hasser (e.g., `hasChildren()`) methods based on the property path (`author`, `children`). These methods are typically used for boolean properties or checking existence.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/property_access.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// ...
class Person
{
    private bool $author = true;
    private array $children = [];

    public function isAuthor(): bool
    {
        return $this->author;
    }

    public function hasChildren(): bool
    {
        return 0 !== count($this->children);
    }
}

$person = new Person();

if ($propertyAccessor->getValue($person, 'author')) {
    var_dump('This person is an author');
}
if ($propertyAccessor->getValue($person, 'children')) {
    var_dump('This person has children');
}
```

