TITLE: Configuring Invokable Factory Service - Symfony PHP Configurator - php
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to configure a service in PHP using Symfony's ContainerConfigurator, linking a service to its invokable factory. Dependencies (NewsletterManager, InvokableNewsletterManagerFactory) must be available. Returns a closure to set up the DI container, registering the factory for NewsletterManager.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/service_container/factories.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// config/services.php
namespace Symfony\Component\DependencyInjection\Loader\Configurator;

use App\Email\NewsletterManager;
use App\Email\NewsletterManagerFactory;

return function(ContainerConfigurator $container): void {
    $services = $container->services();

    $services->set(NewsletterManager::class)
        ->factory(service(InvokableNewsletterManagerFactory::class));
};

```

