TITLE: Enabling ESI Support in Varnish for Symfony
DESCRIPTION: These configurations enable Edge Side Includes (ESI) support in Varnish for Symfony applications by adding necessary headers and parsing responses.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/http_cache/varnish.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: varnish4
CODE:
```
sub vcl_recv {
    // Add a Surrogate-Capability header to announce ESI support.
    set req.http.Surrogate-Capability = "abc=ESI/1.0";
}
```

LANGUAGE: varnish4
CODE:
```
sub vcl_backend_response {
    // Check for ESI acknowledgement and remove Surrogate-Control header
    if (beresp.http.Surrogate-Control ~ "ESI/1.0") {
        unset beresp.http.Surrogate-Control;
        set beresp.do_esi = true;
    }
}
```

