TITLE: Injecting Anonymous Services in Symfony via PHP Configurator
DESCRIPTION: Uses the PHP ContainerConfigurator to define a Foo service that receives an inline AnonymousBar instance as an argument. Dependencies: Symfony DependencyInjection PHP config, ContainerConfigurator. The inline_service() helper is used in the PHP DSL to create an anonymous service. Limitation: explicit autowiring/autoconfiguration must be called per service if needed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/service_container/alias_private.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// config/services.php\nnamespace Symfony\\Component\\DependencyInjection\\Loader\\Configurator;\n\nuse App\\AnonymousBar;\nuse App\\Foo;\n\nreturn function(ContainerConfigurator $container): void {\n    $services = $container->services();\n\n    $services->set(Foo::class)\n        ->args([inline_service(AnonymousBar::class)]);\n};
```

