TITLE: Implementing UserPassword Constraint with PHP Code
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to set up the UserPassword constraint programmatically using PHP code in a model class. Uses ClassMetadata to add the constraint to the oldPassword property.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/reference/constraints/UserPassword.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// src/Form/Model/ChangePassword.php
namespace App\Form\Model;

use Symfony\Component\Security\Core\Validator\Constraints as SecurityAssert;
use Symfony\Component\Validator\Mapping\ClassMetadata;

class ChangePassword
{
    // ...

    public static function loadValidatorData(ClassMetadata $metadata): void
    {
