TITLE: Applying NotEqualTo Constraints using PHP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to apply NotEqualTo constraints using PHP code in a loadValidatorMetadata method. It adds constraints to the firstName and age properties of the Person class.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/reference/constraints/NotEqualTo.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// src/Entity/Person.php
namespace App\Entity;

use Symfony\Component\Validator\Constraints as Assert;
use Symfony\Component\Validator\Mapping\ClassMetadata;

class Person
{
    // ...

    public static function loadValidatorMetadata(ClassMetadata $metadata): void
    {
        $metadata->addPropertyConstraint('firstName', new Assert\NotEqualTo('Mary'));

        $metadata->addPropertyConstraint('age', new Assert\NotEqualTo(
            value: 15,
        ));
    }
}
```

