TITLE: Building Configuration Tree with Parameters Node in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a configuration tree builder with parameters node definitions and validation rules using Symfony's Configuration component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/config/definition.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_26

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
public function addParametersNode(): NodeDefinition
{
    $treeBuilder = new TreeBuilder('parameters');

    $node = $treeBuilder->getRootNode()
        ->isRequired()
        ->requiresAtLeastOneElement()
        ->useAttributeAsKey('name')
        ->arrayPrototype()
            ->children()
                ->scalarNode('value')->isRequired()->end()
            ->end()
        ->end()
    ;

    return $node;
}
```

