TITLE: Adding a Product to a Category from the Inverse Side
DESCRIPTION: Method in the Category entity that shows how to properly add a Product to a Category from the inverse side of the relationship. It ensures the owning side is also updated.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/doctrine/associations.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// src/Entity/Category.php

// ...
class Category
{
    // ...

    public function addProduct(Product $product): self
    {
        if (!$this->products->contains($product)) {
            $this->products[] = $product;
            $product->setCategory($this);
        }

        return $this;
    }
}
```

