TITLE: Configuring PropertyAccessor for Invalid Array Index Exceptions (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use `PropertyAccessorBuilder` to configure the accessor to throw a `NoSuchIndexException` when an invalid array index is accessed, instead of returning null. It also introduces the nullsafe operator `?` within the path (`[age?]`) to prevent the exception and return `null`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/components/property_access.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// ...
$propertyAccessor = PropertyAccess::createPropertyAccessorBuilder()
    ->enableExceptionOnInvalidIndex()
    ->getPropertyAccessor();

$person = [
    'first_name' => 'Wouter',
];

// instead of returning null, the code now throws an exception of type
// Symfony\Component\PropertyAccess\Exception\NoSuchIndexException
$value = $propertyAccessor->getValue($person, '[age]');

// You can avoid the exception by adding the nullsafe operator
$value = $propertyAccessor->getValue($person, '[age?]');
```

