TITLE: Configuring Expression Constraints with PHP Attributes in Symfony
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use PHP attributes to define an Expression constraint on a class property. The constraint ensures that the 'metric' value plus an error margin is less than a threshold value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/blob/7.3/reference/constraints/Expression.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// src/Model/Analysis.php
namespace App\Model;

use Symfony\Component\Validator\Constraints as Assert;

class Analysis
{
    #[Assert\Expression(
        'value + error_margin < threshold',
        values: ['error_margin' => 0.25, 'threshold' => 1.5],
    )]
    private float $metric;

    // ...
}
```

